# PlaceCardView

## Summary

Renders a wedding place card: an optional uppercase event-title kicker, the guest name in large serif type, a gold rule, then the table name and an optional italic message. It is the shared stationery visual — both the PlaceCard card definition and the planner's print sheet render it, so the card on screen and the printed cell stay identical. Sizing is container-query driven, so the same component reads well as a large isolated card, a small fitted tile, or a print-sheet cell.

## Import

```js
import { PlaceCardView } from '../components/card-views';
```

## Template Usage

All args are optional strings; missing ones are simply omitted (the name falls back to "Guest Name"):

```gjs
<PlaceCardView
  @eventTitle={{@model.eventTitle}}
  @guestName={{g.fullName}}
  @tableName={{t.name}}
  @message={{@model.seatingMessage}}
/>
```
